# Copy this file to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and fill in values. Both are gitignored, so your
# secrets are never committed. NEVER prefix any of these with NEXT_PUBLIC_ — that would expose them
# to the browser. In production (Vercel), set the UPSTASH_* vars in the dashboard, UNQUOTED.

# ── Ghost trails (museum "other visitors" presence) ─────────────────────────────
# Upstash Redis REST credentials. Optional: without them the site still works — ghosts just fall
# back to procedural wisps. Create a free database at https://console.upstash.com and copy the
# REST URL + token (use the REST values, not the redis:// connection string).
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=

# ── GitHub project sync (local only) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only needed to run `npm run sync:github` LOCALLY — it lifts the GitHub API rate limit (60 → 5000
# req/hr) for the deep dependency scan. The scheduled GitHub Action uses the built-in GITHUB_TOKEN
# and needs no secret. Create a fine-grained token at GitHub → Settings → Developer settings →
# Fine-grained tokens, with Repository access: Public repositories (read-only), short expiration.
GH_TOKEN=
